         /waves at Ishtarra</P><P>Seen ya in the Bazaar the other night sporting your epic, glad the eye served somebody well. :-)</P><P>I loved the Bazaar.  No more shouting or OOC`ing for a PC (and never getting an answer, of course).  No more having to shift-uparrow & constantly spam.</P><P>Due to the price wars currently going on I was able to update some of Mysker's old stuff.  Not exactly exceptional, but he now has Grey Flesh leggings, Coeterie General's Cloak, Chetari Wardstaff, and some other stuff.. minus their proper spelling.</P><P>My suggestion is this:</P><P>Each starting city, as well as misc. zones like EC/WC, has a large number of empty buildings.  Both upstairs and down.</P><P>Making use of these for Bazaar trader locations would:<BR>--1.) Reduce server load & chance of a zone dropping.<BR>--2.) Reduce Video lag. Most players would be inside of buildings.<BR>--3.) Reduce the chance of players going LD in, or upon entering, the zones.<BR>--4.) Be more player friendly.</P><P>While the Bazaar would still remain the prime location due to no faction problems, the bank, and merchants.</P><P>Hmm, I wonder if an option like this would be used if ever added.  Or if they could just designate specific semi-open zones like EC/WC, GFay for additional Bazaar locations.</P><P>The number of people in the Bazaar zone is only going to grow.</P><P>~Mysk</P><P>===<BR>-/\- 57 Dark Elven Defiler -/\-<BR>--,-`-{@ Tunare Server @}-,-`--<BR><a href="http://www.myskyra.net/forums" target="_blank">http://www.myskyra.net/forums</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
